		<title>13THE GROVE HOSPITAL</title>
		<content>   The Grove Hospital is on the        
 outskirts of the village of Shardlow. 
 It is situated near the site of the   
 old Shardlow workhouse which was      
 demolished in December 1982.          
   The Grove is a N.H.S. small hospital
 for elderly patients. There are       
 seventy two patients at the moment who
 are looked after by Mrs. Keefe,       
 Matron, one hundred nurses, four      
 kitchen staff, eleven cleaners, three 
 porters and two laundry workers.      
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
